article.description: — Justin Wilson scored 18 points as Northwestern State beat New Orleans 92-67 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Wilson scores 18, Northwestern State downs New Orleans 92-67
article.linkText: Wilson scores 18, Northwestern State downs New Orleans 92-67
article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- — Justin Wilson scored 18 points as Northwestern State beat New Orleans 92-67 on Saturday night. Wilson also contributed 11 rebounds for the Demons (5-13, 3-2 Southland Conference). Cliff Davis scored 16 points while shooting 3 of 7 from the field and 10 for 10 from the line. Braelon Bush was 6 of 13 shooting (1 for 3 from 3-point range) to finish with 15 points. Tyson Jackson led the Privateers (7-11, 2-3) in scoring, finishing with 16 points and eight rebounds. Jordan Johnson added 13 points for New Orleans. Jah Short also had eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
